      <h4>Describe an analogy to describe HTML and CSS?</h4>
      <p>Html is akin to the builder of the website, it defines the structure using individual elements. It does not have any visual appeal which is where CSS comes in. CSS allows you to to define how to style these individual elements. You can assign a special class to multiple elements or you can assign a unique Id to single out individual elements that you would like to style in a particular way. CSS can be thought of as the artist(or stylist), it takes the elements of the structure and styles them in a way to be more visually appealing or make the website responsive to devices with different screen sizes.</p>
      <p>If you were building a house CSS would be the paint or the floorings or the fittings and HTML would be the structure of the house.</p>
