      <h4>Describe what the DOM is and an example of how you might interact with it.</h4>
      <p>The DOM is a separate representation of the web page once it is loaded. It is created by your web browser and is different to HTML. The HTML DOM is like a family tree of all of the HTML elements in the form of JS objects. This allows us to access each of these elements and run a program or script on that element so you are able to dynamically alter the structure or style of the web page after it is loaded.</p>
      <p>For example you now have the ability to change the background colour of your webpage based on a specific action that you can define in Javascript. For example using the DOM and Javascript you could implement this; “When I double click the mouse access the background-colour from the body of the document and change the colour”.</p>
